  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">HIV &amp; AIDS  Prevention Programme for MSM &amp; SW in Kenya</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Although sub-Saharan Africa represents just over 10% of the world&apos;&apos;s population, it is home to over two-thirds of all people living with HIV. Men who have sex with men or sex workers have disproportionately high levels of HIV, accounting for almost a third of all new HIV infections. Widows and Orphans runs an HIV and AIDS prevention programme for people affected in Kenya. The project provides targeted and appropriate HIV testing and counselling, as well as providing condoms, suitable lubricants, and education materials to help people reduce their risk of HIV. The project ensures that these marginalised groups can protect themselves from HIV, get tested, and if positive, are not stigmatised or discriminated against when they use mainstream care and support services. There are also opportunities for vocational training and access to micro-credit schemes for this vulnerable group.</narrative>
  </description>
